title: For Sale:  [PRICE DROP] 1986 Norinco MAK-90 w/Timber Smith Furniture, upgraded trigger, mags, ammo, etc
postcontent: Up for sale is my amazing condition 1986 made Norinco MAK-90 AKM. The guy I bought it from didn't fire it, it looked like the guy he bought it from didn't either. I only put 10 rounds through her, and it's in absolutely amazing condition. Barely has the race mark from the safety on the frame, and internals look brand new. I don't think this thing has had more than 50 rounds through it since it was made, honestly.This is a ban-era AKM, that was made with the thum bhole stock, the muzzle thread removed & the muzzle device taken off like all of the rest of the rifles imported around that time. This gun shoots AWESOME. It's extremely smooth. ONLY reason I'm selling it, is due to an old shoulder injury heavier rifles are harder for me to hold up and fire comfortably. Something this nice deserves to be enjoyed and taken to the range, not sitting in my safe and only coming out every few months eh.This rifle comes with gorgeous (and expensive) red Timber Wolf furniture installed and a Tapco trigger installed, the original thumb hole furniture and original trigger, 2 magazines (Brand new 30 round P-Mag and brand new 20 round P-mag), 30 rounds of PPU 123gr PSP copper ammo (no steel, good to shoot at any range), a standard military style sling, and a soft case.I'm asking $800 FIRM for this. These things usually sell beat up for $850, but for this price you're getting a near mint MAK-90 with a brand new set of $160 furniture, mags, ammo, and an upgraded trigger. This deal is priced low to sell fast.FIRM means if you text/email me with a lower offer you will be ignored. I'm not new to this, don't insult me with a lowball. Not looking for trades on this one, cash is king. Best way to contact me is by texting REDACTED at any time or shooting me a PM on here.Face to face deals only, must be 18+.
